    "caption": "Rolling in mud isn't being dirty — it's being brilliant.",
    "shortDescription": "Pigs don't sweat the way we do, so on a hot day they wade straight into the nearest mud puddle and stay there. That mud dries into a cool, crispy shell that keeps them comfortable for hours. They're also shockingly clever — pigs can learn to play simple video games and figure out puzzles faster than dogs. Fun fact: A pig's nose is so sensitive it can sniff out food buried thirty centimeters underground."
